@node Q1 "DayDream BBS FAQ - How do I install DayDream?"

@{b}How do I install DayDream?@{ub}
--------------------------

You  must de-archive  DayDream to the directory  into which you want in to
be  installed.   Then  you  must  run  the  supplied  installer script called
InstallDD,  this will create some required directories and add some essential
commands to your user-startup.

@endnode


@node Q2 "DayDream BBS FAQ - How do I create a SysOp account?"

@{b}
How do I create a SysOp account?@{ub}
--------------------------------

This is either done directly via the supplied installer script, or you can do
is manually from CLI/Shell by typing the following:

   run <>NIL: server
   run <>NIL: daydream n2 lc

    This will start a local login.  You must proceed as a new user and create
your  SysOp  account  in this way.  Once you've reached the main menu, select
Local  UserED from the menu bar.  Select C for current user, then select L to
alter  the  Security  setting, change it to 255.  This has created your SysOp
account.
    To  skip  the  login  delay  when  doing  a  local login, use 'run <>NIL:
daydream n2 lo',  this  selects an  operator login and you don't have to type
your account name and password.

@endnode


@node Q3 "DayDream BBS FAQ - Why when I try to upload something, it says not enough free space?"

@{b}Why when I try to upload something, it says not enough free space?@{ub}
------------------------------------------------------------------

 It's  not  that you  don't have enough space, it's  that it can't find the
directory  to  put  it in (because it dosen't exist).  You specify the upload
path in DayDream.CFG in the CONFERENCES.DAT section.  eg:

!CONFERENCES.DAT
CONF_NUMB..... 1
CONF_NAME..... RořkIEs
CONF_PATH..... DayDream:NewUsers/
CONF_FILEAREAS 1                   <-- Must be 1 or more for uploads to work.
CONF_UPLOADSTO 0
CONF_MSGBASES. 1
CONF_COMMENTS. 1
CONF_ULPATH... DayDream:NewUserConf/NewFiles/  <-- This is where files will go
CONF_NSAREAS.. -                                   after uploading. Please note:
. . .                                              MUST end with / or :
. . .                                              ~~~~
. . .

@endnode


@node Q4 "DayDream BBS FAQ - Why can't I flag files for downloading?"

@{b}Why can't I flag files for downloading?@{ub}
---------------------------------------

 You  need to specify  the download path separately.  The  file you need to
create  is  called DayDream:<conference path>/Data/PATHS.DAT.  Just use Ed or
Cygnus  to  enter  the  FULL  path of 1 or more directories that files can be
downloaded from, from the specified conference. All paths MUST end with / or :

@endnode


@node Q5 "DayDream BBS FAQ - How should I number my conferences and message bases?"

@{b}
How should I number my conferences and message bases?@{ub}
-----------------------------------------------------

 The  numbering  system is very flexible, but the  standard way of doing it
is like this:

Conf 1
Base 1
Base 2
Base 3
*
Conf 2
Base 1
*
Conf 3
*
Conf 4
Base 1
~
    You could leave Conf 2 out, and just have 3 conferences numbered 1, 3 and
4, and it would work ok.
    You  should  have at least 1 message base per conference, for comments to
sysop messages entered with command C.
@endnode


@node Q6 "DayDream BBS FAQ - Why is it that when I ask for a file listing, it says only 1 area in use, when in fact I have more?"

@{b}Why is it that when I ask for a file listing, it says only 1 area in use, when in fact I have more?@{ub}
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  That message is stored  in the file  DayDream:Display/iso/FileCatalogs.GFX
(and  .TXT).   You  should  create  a directory in your conference directory:
DayDream:<conference  path>/Display/Iso,  and  then,  using  an  ansi or text
editor,  edit the file FileCatalogs.GFX so that when displayed, it lists your
file areas.

@endnode


@node Q7 "DayDream BBS FAQ - How can I get it to put the file in the right area?"

@{b}How can I get it to put the file in the right area?@{ub}
---------------------------------------------------

 You  must configure  DayDream to ask the user  (after upload) where to put
each   file.    To   do   this,  you  need  to  edit  DayDream.CFG.   In  the
CONFERENCES.DAT   section   there   is  a  line  in  each  conference  called
'CONF_ASKDEST..   N'.   Change  the  N  to  a  Y, that's all (don't forget to
recompile DayDream.CFG though).

@endnode


@node Q8 "DayDream BBS FAQ - Insane messagenumbers etc."

@{b}I added a  new conference with a message base, and when I join the
conference, it comes up with insane numbers for highest and lowest messages,
why is this?@{ub}


DayDream is uncertain of the new LastReadPointers and the LastScannedPointers
for all users, you need to run the program 'FixBases' in DayDream:Utils/ and
this will take care of the problem.

@endnode


@node Q9 "DayDream BBS FAQ - I can't get SModem and Hydra to work properly, what's wrong?"

@{b}I can't get SModem and Hydra to work properly, what's wrong?@{ub}
------------------------------------------------------------

Make sure that the serial device you are using is opened in SHARED access mode.
(IO_MODE....... S  in IO-DEVICES.DAT)

Also make sure that the path to SModem and DDHydra executables is in your
systems path. ('Path DayDream:Utils/ ADD' should do just that.)

@endnode

@node Q10 "DayDream BBS FAQ - What are the modem strings for my modem?"

These strings are collected from various DayDream sysops and work fine
for them, if they do not work properly for you, then don't blame me.
If your modem is not listed here, maybe you could try with a modem from
the same manufacturer.

@endnode



