@node Q11 "DayDream BBS FAQ - When I upload something, it says file already here, what's up?"

@{b}When I upload something, it says file already here, what's up?@{ub}
--------------------------------------------------------------

Check your @{b}<ConferenceName>/Data/Paths.DAT@{ub} so that it exists and is
correctly configured. Look in the manual on how to configure this.

@endnode


@node Q12 "DayDream BBS FAQ - My BBS doesn't run any arexx doors, what's up ?" 

@{b}My BBS doesn't run any arexx doors, what's up ?@{ub}
-----------------------------------------------

Make sure RexxMast is running. (The DayDream installer should take care
of this)

Make sure that the command 'RX' can be found in your current system path
(Usually this program is located in the sys:rexxc/ drawer)

As a last try, you can try putting the RX program in your C: directory.

@endnode


@node Q13 "DayDream BBS FAQ - My BBS doesn't run any arexx doors, what's up ?" 

@{b}
I'm having trouble with my XPR transfers. What to do ?@{ub}
------------------------------------------------------

First of all check your serial.device. Always try the origial device from
commodore before you try out the optimized/hacked and other devices.

Also check your serial prefs (Prefs/Serial). Check the baudrate and buffersize
settings. 

Check your modem configuration. Try out the settings supplied with this FAQ
if it matches your modem type, and if they don't, try out the general one.

Read your modems manual. Twice. Then read it again, and check all your
modemstring settings. If all else fails, contact me or anyone that runs
a DayDream BBS with the same modem.

@endnode

@node Introduction "DayDream BBS FAQ - Introduction"

This document is intended to help you as a user to troubleshoot some of
the common problems encounterd while using DayDream BBS.

I really hope that you will help to maintain this FAQ with new questions/answers
and that you will recieve some guidance through this FAQ.

A very big thank you to @{B}Stefan Holmes@{UB} for writing the first DayDream FAQ, but
who unfortunetly is unable to update this. Some of the questions in here were
originally aswered by him and all I did was to AmigaGuide:ize them.

If you have working modem configurations that is not included in here,
please send them to me so that I can include them here.  Please send a
full profile plus the part from your DayDream.CFG concerning modem settings.

                      Send more material for this FAQ to:

